1
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,160
No, I hate those episodes in shows.

2
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:08,480
Where at the end they say, "It was just a dream, it’s not real."

3
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:11,360
It’s all in the actors' heads. How annoying is that?

4
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:12,360
Yeah, right.

5
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:20,680
Hey, aren’t they dressed too warmly?
-I don’t know.

6
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,840
Believe me, your mom has already thrown me off balance.

7
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:24,160
Why, what did she do to you this time?

8
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:27,400
No, it’s not something specific. It’s in general.
She always has something to say,

9
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,720
She always makes me feel
like I’m not a good enough mom.

10
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,640
Well, over the years you learn to filter her.

11
00:00:32,439 --> 00:00:34,800
You’ll learn to ignore the faces, the raised eyebrows.

12
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:36,840
No, it’s not just about the faces
and the raised eyebrows, babe.

13
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,280
She always makes me feel
like I’m killing the kids.

14
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,600
She doesn’t really mean it.
-Yeah, she always has something to say.

15
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,560
It’s hot, the kids are dressed too much,
they’ll get a rash.

16
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,680
It’s cold, they’re not dressed, they’ll get pneumonia.

17
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:49,160
Don’t give the kid spices
until she’s three, you’re killing her.

18
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:51,640
And isn’t that true?
-Of course it’s not true,

19
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:54,200
but that doesn’t stop her from saying it.
She also doesn’t know what’s right,

20
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:56,560
but she only knows that what I’m doing is wrong.

21
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:01,960
Sit down, babe, you’re a great mom.
-Right? I think so too.

22
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:03,440
I’m a great mom, right?
-Of course.

23
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,360
Just don’t say that in front of her
because it’ll just encourage her more.

24
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:16,920
Look at me, look at me and...

25
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:33,280
Can you at least tell him
to shut that annoying thing off?

26
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,120
Shut that annoying thing off.

27
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:43,080
He didn’t shut it.
-Babe, let him eat in peace. Okay?

28
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,160
What peace? I can’t eat
with that annoying noise.

29
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:48,200
Who even hears that?
-Aren’t you supposed to teach him, as a parent?

30
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,480
Do me a favor, let his mom
teach him. Now I’m hungry, okay?

31
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,320
Do whatever you want.

32
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:59,360
Why like that?
-Not like that. I said do whatever you want.

33
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,760
Fine.
-Yeah.

34
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:05,040
Sorry to interrupt. Where’s Uncle Adam?

35
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,800
He’s in reserve duty. Maybe he’ll drop by later.

36
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:14,160
Didn’t you teach her not to talk with her mouth full?
-Of course I told her.

37
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,800
Sweetie, if you talk with your mouth full,

38
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:20,080
you’ll choke and die.
-Mom.

39
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:21,840
Do you want to kill the kid?

40
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:24,840
Sit down, sit down.
-Riki, I’m asking, enough with this.

41
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,720
Enough with what?
-I can’t take this anymore.

42
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:31,080
Riki, enough. I’m a great mom. Okay?
-What happened? What did I say?

43
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,080
That she’s killing the kid, maybe?

44
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,760
No, it’s important to me that you understand I’m a great mom.

45
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,000
I care about their health,
I care about their education,

46
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:40,520
everything is perfectly fine.
-I’m sure of it.

47
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:44,160
I’m really sorry. I probably misunderstood.

48
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:49,200
It’s okay, everything’s fine. I forgive you.

49
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:53,600
Alright, let’s watch something now.
-Here it comes.

50
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:58,280
You all heard the silly fight
between Michal and Itamar, right?

51
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,640
Why silly?
-Because it was silly.

52
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,560
You don’t interfere.

53
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:06,920
So, as a great mom,
what do you think is right?

54
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,160
Should the kid play by the table or not?

55
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:12,960
What seems more educationally correct?

56
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,680
Take your time, thaw another slacker.

57
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,000
Sit down, come here for a sec.

58
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,320
Eat, eat.

59
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,640
Do you see what you did?

60
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:31,760
Do you see what you did? Idiot.

61
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,200
What, babe, it's fine.
-No, it's not fine.

62
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:44,440
I know her longer than you have
and I know where this is going.

63
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,960
Where to?
-To the import, Shai, we're going home, now!

64
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,000
At best.

65
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:50,440
So what, what do you want? I'm not supposed to solve

66
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:53,640
your mom's riddle?
-I told you it would just encourage her.

67
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:56,080
Babe, you're exaggerating, right?
-That's what you think.

68
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:59,560
No, I think a person
should do what they feel,

69
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,680
I feel like Michal is right.

70
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,400
Riki, what you did to Shani just now is really not okay.

71
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:11,920
What's the problem? If she says she's
a great mom, then it's just a compliment.

72
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:15,720
It's not like I asked her
to make eggplant spread with liver flavor.

73
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,720
Shh...
-Have you seen Itamar?

74
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:23,480
He's in the bathroom.
-Come on, eat the shakshuka. It's still warm.

75
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:29,520
And Shani, that really wasn't a compliment.
I think you're a great mom.

76
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:33,160
Thanks.
-And let's eat because this shakshuka is still fresh.

77
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:37,560
Eat up, eat up.
-And about what you said, you don't have to thicken it for me.

78
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,440
Sit down.
-Actually, I'd love to thicken it for you, Riki.

79
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,680
Yeah?
-I think in this case,

80
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,440
Michal is right.
-Thanks, babe.

81
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,160
Michal...

82
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,240
Why are you doing that?
-Doing what?

83
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,360
The eyebrow raise.
-Filter, filter.

84
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:54,880
You're saying Michal, who isn't even
a mom to a Chihuahua, is right?

85
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,040
What's wrong? I've always wanted a Chihuahua.

86
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:00,520
So Michal is right?
-Yeah, yeah, Riki. She's right.

87
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:03,000
I think in this case, Itamar needs to understand

88
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:06,400
that part of parenting is also teaching his son.
-Oh!

89
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,360
So Itamar isn't connected.
-No, I didn't say that.

90
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:13,880
So I failed to connect with Itamar.
-Riki, I... I didn't...

91
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,320
I didn't say that.

92
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,600
Let it go.
-Ew...

93
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:26,760
What, did the burp make you laugh?
Do you also like a little fart? Yeah?

94
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:35,320
Rivka...
-Did you see the little brat?

95
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,400
Rivka...
-And I'm always the one who's wrong.

96
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:41,360
My connection isn't good and I should just stay quiet.
-Rivka!

97
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:45,000
Did you see how the North African side jumped out of her?
-Rivka!

98
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,440
Okay, fine, I know.

99
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:54,080
Family. I'll talk to her.
-Thanks.

100
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,360
But she needs to come here.

101
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:04,400
Sit down, babe, let's try to minimize the damage.
-Yeah, yeah, sure.

102
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:07,240
Just remind me: to minimize means
I need to go apologize.

103
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,760
Babe,
-What babe, I'm already tired of this,

104
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,600
you don't understand she's painting me as a monster

105
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:14,200
and in the end, I'm the one who has to apologize
for being portrayed as a monster.

106
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,720
Babe, you're not a monster.
-Thanks, babe, thanks.

107
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,960
I just... I meant to...
never mind, okay, thanks.

108
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,720
A distinction in the herd, just so you know.
-Thanks. Thank you very much.

109
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:27,440
So come on, explain to me what's the fuss.
-You're in the Knesset on the balcony and she's right,

110
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,640
and you have a lot to learn from her, and she's right.

111
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,000
Yeah, because she's right.

112
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,040
Yeah.
-She's right.

113
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,280
Maybe I'll also get down on all fours
and kiss her feet.

114
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,280
That could be a really nice addition
but you don't have to, you don't have to.

115
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,080
Okay, move.

116
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,880
I did my best.
-And I prepared the ground.

117
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:49,040
Do you think it'll work?
-No chance.

118
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,960
Adam.
-Hey, Shabbat Shalom.

119
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,040
Where's Mom?
-On the balcony.

120
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:58,800
Oh, so Dad, is it really okay that I brought a guest?

121
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:02,000
What a question, of course.
-Come on.

122
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:16,080
I'm sorry the conversation got to this point.

123
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,480
Me too.

124
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,920
Still, you have an edge over me in motherhood.

125
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,040
You're doing a great job too.

126
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:34,760
Come on
Come on

127
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:41,800
Come on
Come on

128
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,800
Wow
Wow

129
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:54,760
My dad Pinchas, my brother Shai,
my sister-in-law Michal. Meet Matadel.

130
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,440
So beautiful.
-Shh.

131
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,000
Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

132
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,960
Itamar, come here for a sec.

133
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,840
So, what do you guys have today?

134
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:06,320
Oh, okay. Where's Mom?

135
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,720
She's on the balcony right now! Sit down, we're faking a reunion.

136
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,480
Hey, I'm Itamar, his brother.

137
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,400
Nice to meet you.
-Matadel.

138
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,080
Matadel sounds familiar. Oh, they're coming.

139
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:23,400
Hello, Mom.
-Hi, my sweet.

140
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:28,720
Pinchas...
-I hope it's okay

141
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,760
that Matadel is staying for lunch. Right?

142
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,559
Of course, what a question! You're invited.

143
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,440
See?
-Thanks.

144
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:41,240
Matadel is from the base and I gave her a ride home.

145
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:45,760
I was thinking of stopping by for a snack from the shlaykler.

146
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,880
Funny name.
-Matadel?

147
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,320
Shlaykler.

148
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:58,240
So you guys aren't friends or anything?
Not that I'm judging...

149
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:02,600
Judging what?
-He can date whoever he wants.

150
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:07,240
Just that he should get married in a few weeks.

151
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,200
After he finds the right girl.

152
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:13,760
Should we go to the table?
-Uncle Adam.

153
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,440
Come on.

154
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,840
It's calming. They're not a couple.

155
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,760
What? Why are you doing this to me?

156
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,960
Riki?
-You come into my house and do this to me?

157
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,880
Any moment now you'll start rolling your eyes at me.

158
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,080
I'm really sorry, Riki, for having my own opinions.

159
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:39,040
Stupid opinions, that's what you have.
-Stupid opinions?

160
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:42,520
Stupid. Yes.
I treat you like my daughter.

161
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:46,480
You come into my house and act like this?

162
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:49,640
What, are you spitting in my face?
-Is this how you treat your daughter?

163
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,160
Pinchas, look what she's doing to me in front of the grandkids!

164
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,040
Now, Shai, we're going home. Enough!

165
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,000
What, honey, it's fine.
-No, it's not fine.

166
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,520
I know her longer than you
and I know where this is going.

167
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:14,280
Where? To import, Shai, we're going home
right now!" at best.

168
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:17,360
Come on, so what do you want?
How am I supposed to solve

169
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:20,400
your mom's riddle?
-I told you it would just encourage her.

170
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,840
Honey, you're exaggerating, right?
-That's what you think.

171
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:26,480
No, I think a person
should do what they feel.

172
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:29,800
And I feel Michal is right.
-This won't end well.

173
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:33,360
So what, like? I need to do
this reverse psychology,

174
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:37,320
like you know what's right to do
and you do the opposite?

175
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:40,320
So be it. Itamar is right.

176
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:44,200
Riki, what you did to Shani just now is really not okay.

177
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:48,800
What's the problem? If she says she's
a great mom, it's just a compliment.

178
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:52,560
It's not like I asked her
to make eggplant spread with liver flavor.

179
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:55,480
Shh...
-Did you see Itamar?

180
00:10:55,800 --> 00:11:00,320
He's in the bathroom.
-Come eat from the shlaykler, they're still warm.

181
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:06,360
And Shabi, that really wasn't nice.
I think you're a great mom.

182
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,400
Thanks.
-Now let's eat because these knishes

183
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,680
are still fresh. Eat up, eat up.

184
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:14,880
And about what Tzod said, you don't have to defend me.
-Shabi!

185
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,840
Actually, I'd love to defend you on that, Riki.
_ Yeah.
Yeah.

186
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:24,120
I think in the argument between Michal and Itamar
the one who's right is Itamar.

187
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:28,040
What about Itamar?
-That's true, but it was easy.

188
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:31,360
Now comes the harder and more important part:

189
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:34,120
Why is Itamar right?

190
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:37,840
I don't know.

191
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:42,880
Because, because the child's mom
is the one who needs to raise him.

192
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:46,520
No, no, no, no, no. No, great mom.

193
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:52,080
If the kid stops playing at the table,
then he'll start acting out,

194
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,640
start bothering, and then he needs to be raised.

195
00:11:56,720 --> 00:12:00,720
But like this, if he stays quiet,
he'll connect on his own.

196
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:05,000
What, why are you going "ummm"?
Is what I'm saying not true?

197
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:09,200
No, that's not true. What?
Playing at the table means a connected kid?

198
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,520
And when my daughter apologized
for bothering and spoke with her mouth full,

199
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,520
you're saying my daughter isn't raised well?

200
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,960
You won't raise your voice in my house.

201
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,000
Rivka.
-Shabi.

202
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,440
Are you listening?
-Did I raise my voice?

203
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:20,360
I didn't raise my voice.

204
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:23,680
I'm just trying to save my granddaughters' lives

205
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:30,080
like any good grandma would.
-Me? I'm killing again.

206
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:33,720
You get it? I'm killing again?
-Shabi.

207
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:40,200
Why all these dramas? Why?
I'm not feeling good, I'm telling you.

208
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:43,960
Yuck!
-Now it's better.

209
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,800
Did you see that cheeky one?
-Shabi.

210
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:55,240
No, I'm always wrong and my parenting
isn't good and I need to be quiet.

211
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,400
Shabi.
-Did you see how her Moroccan side came out?

212
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,560
Shabi!
-Yeah, yeah. I know.

213
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:01,160
I need to go talk to her.
-Thanks.

214
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,080
I don't want to.
-Shabi.

215
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,320
She's the one who needs to apologize.

216
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:11,120
Rivka, what's with you? Why do you always
look at the glass half empty?

217
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:15,440
What are you talking about?
-She's trying to please you.

218
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,760
Even if she doesn't think so,
she told you she's on Itamar's side

219
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,720
just because he's your son.
And you don't see all that?

220
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:24,000
But...
-No buts. She's trying.

221
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,600
Okay, fine, fine.

222
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:30,880
Alright, I agree. It's family.

