00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:39,520
The second...
-Rivka, one bride on one Sabbath,

226
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:44,280
and the first one is a bit too much.
-Okay, fine.

227
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:46,400
No problem?

228
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,480
No problem.
-Okay.

229
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,640
I want to go home.
-Wait a second.

230
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,640
Can I?
-Sure.

231
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:01,280
Shabi, I'm really sorry
that the conversation got to this point.

232
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,040
Me too.

233
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:08,680
Regarding motherhood, I think
you're doing a good job.

234
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,400
Thanks.

235
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,760
And you too, Riki,

236
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:22,280
I mean, you have a big advantage over me in motherhood,

237
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:26,240
and I'm just trying.
-Yeah.

238
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:31,360
Boi
Come on

239
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,480
Yeah.

240
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,680
Mom, hey.
-Hey.

241
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,320
It's so nice you could make it.

242
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:45,880
I hope it's okay you brought a guest.

243
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:48,520
Of course, no question about it.

244
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,200
Come on in.

245
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:57,720
Hi.
-Hi.

246
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:02,640
Matadel, meet my mom Rivka. My sister-in-law Shani.

247
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:06,120
Matadel is from the base! I gave her a ride home.

248
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:10,160
I was thinking about stopping by for a snack from the shlaykler.

249
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:13,480
Funny name.
-Matadel?

250
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:17,760
Shlaykler.
-Uncle Adam.

251
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:24,520
What a coincidence, his girlfriend is Ethiopian.
-First of all, she's not his girlfriend,

252
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:29,320
and you don't say Ethiopian.
She's Israeli of Ethiopian descent.

253
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:31,520
You don't have to say everything you see.

254
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,400
It's a matter of upbringing.
-Rivka, I'm asking you

255
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:37,360
not to educate my daughter.
I'm her mom, and I'll decide if it's needed.

256
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:41,040
But if my granddaughter is acting
like a primitive from the jungle,

257
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:44,040
Sorry, Matadel, then I do need to educate her.

258
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:47,480
You just called my daughter primitive.
Are you for real?

259
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:50,400
She's not to blame. It's because her mom is primitive.

260
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:54,480
Shai, come on, we're leaving.
-Yeah, go back to the jungle you came from.

261
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:58,040
Riki, you need therapy.
-You need a reboot.

262
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,320
Enough!

263
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,720
How am I supposed to solve your mom's riddle?

264
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,800
I told you it would just encourage her.

265
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:16,320
Babe, you're exaggerating, right?
-That's what you think.

266
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,720
No, I think a person
should do what they feel,

267
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,200
and I feel Michal is right.
-This won't end well.

268
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:26,720
So what, like? I have to do
this reverse psychology thing,

269
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:30,880
like you know what's right to do
and you do the opposite?

270
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,440
Fine, Itamar is right.

271
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,720
And this could lead to another disaster.

272
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,160
Can I interrupt for a second?

273
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,000
Will it help if I say no?
-Not at all.

274
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:42,440
Listen, sweetie, it's a lose-lose situation.

275
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:46,160
You're heading for a dead end and the situation is a mess.
But there's also a third way.

276
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,240
What third way?
It's either you're right or Michal is right?

277
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,520
Don't play at all. You're not ready to take a stand,

278
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,600
you don't get involved, you're like the UN. That's it.

279
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,360
Come on, Mom brought out more shlaykler.
Let's go before Dad finishes them off.

280
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,520
Hold on, I'm in the bathroom. Moshe! It's not sitting well.

281
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:01,480
Come on, babe, let's head back.

282
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:07,520
It's not like I asked her
to make eggplant spread with liver flavor.

283
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:10,240
Shhh..
-Have you seen Itamar?

284
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:11,319
He's in the bathroom.

285
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,280
Come eat the shlaykler, they're still warm.

286
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:21,400
And Shani, it really wasn't intentional.
I think you're a great mom.

287
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:24,920
Thanks.
-And let's eat because these shlaykler are still fresh.

288
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:29,280
Eat up, eat up.
-And about what you said, you don't have to thicken it for me.

289
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,040
Okay.

290
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:39,280
What is it?
-What is what?

291
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:42,320
You're not answering me?
-About what?

292
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:46,760
K'
Oh, it's some kind of game.
-What game, Riki?

293
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,080
Rivka, relax.

294
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:57,720
Wow, it's so quiet. We can eat in peace.

295
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:02,440
Yuck.
-That was the pressure, babe.

296
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:05,560
It was sitting here.
-How's the shlaykler today?

297
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,320
You're asking me?
-Yeah.

298
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,920
Like always.
-Tasty or not tasty?

299
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:20,960
You can't mistake it, it's Riki Rosen's shlaykler.

300
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,720
She's doing it on purpose, she's not answering me.

301
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:27,320
Right?
-Riki, is there something you want me to say?

302
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:28,960
Enough!
-Rivka.

303
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:29,880
No, no.

304
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,800
That's enough for me.
-Calm down. Rivka!

305
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,400
Respect, sis.
-That was my idea, babe.

306
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:39,280
Okay...
-Wait, it's not over yet.

307
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:46,800
Did you see what she did to me?
-Rivka, you see the half-eaten cake.

308
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:50,560
Stop annoying me
with those metaphors of yours, Pinchas.

309
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:54,320
She's trying.
-Trying to drive me crazy.

310
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:57,520
Rivka, let’s go back to the table.
-Pinchas, there will be consequences,

311
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,760
I'm telling you, there will be consequences.

312
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,440
She knows she's being heard. Huh?

313
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,480
Come on
Come here

314
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:06,560
These knishes, I’m telling you,
they’re like seeds,

315
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:09,440
you eat and eat and eat, and there's still room for more.

316
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:13,400
If you're a great mom, what does that say about me?

317
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:17,080
What?
-If you're the great mom

318
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:21,920
with the excellent parenting methods,
then where does that leave me?

319
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:26,480
Riki, you're a great mom.
-The knishes will cool down...

320
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:30,040
And you raised wonderful sons.
-You can heat them in the microwave.

321
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:35,240
But parenting methods have changed, Riki...
-And for the worse. What does that mean,

322
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:39,800
that my methods are outdated? What?
-Not exactly.

323
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:43,080
So back then it wasn't win-win for parenting?
-Not exactly.

324
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,840
So what does that mean?
-Mom.

325
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:51,520
Hey there.
-Adam, Adam, my sweet.

326
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,240
So nice you came.

327
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:58,640
I hope it’s okay I brought a guest.
-Of course, what a question.

328
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,400
What’s the question anyway?
-Come on.

329
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:06,760
You see, this is the result of my parenting.
Look at this sweet and polite kid.

330
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:14,400
Oh! What’s this?
-She’s just a hitchhiker.

331
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:18,760
I’ll wait in the car.
-Mom...

332
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,920
Riki!
-What, now I’m also racist?

333
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,880
Mom!
-Shai, I’m asking you,

334
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:29,960
you and your wife, just be quiet for a bit,
we’ve heard enough of your opinions today.

335
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:33,080
What happened, Riki? Do you have a problem with Adam's girlfriend?

336
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:36,560
No! I have a problem with you.

337
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:43,640
Since you entered this house
I told Pinchas you’re a real pain!

338
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:46,640
Excuse me? Okay, Shai, let’s go home. Now!

339
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,360
Enough! Come on, girls, let’s go,
leave the food, let’s go.

340
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,960
And that’s not true.
-Of course it’s not true,

341
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:04,480
but that doesn’t stop her from saying it.
She also doesn’t know what’s right,

342
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:07,000
but she knows
that only what I do is wrong.

343
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:10,680
Sit down, babe, you’re a great mom.
-Right?

344
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:13,200
I think so too. I’m a great mom. Right?

345
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,160
Of course.

346
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:18,600
Just don’t say that in front of her,
because that will only encourage her more.

347
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,880
What, so you want me to
make her feel like she’s right, or what?

348
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:26,000
No, find something in the middle, neutral.

349
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:30,240
Neutral. With your mom, nothing will help anymore.
-That’s true.

350
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,360
I just want to remind you
that my mom took a self-defense course

351
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,080
a few weeks ago and graduated with honors.

352
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,840
I just want to remind you
that I’m younger than her.

353
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,120
Great, but my mom
has been pounding schnitzels for forty years,

354
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,840
so she has the muscles of a Georgian weightlifter.

355
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:47,400
I don’t care. I’ll tear her apart.

356
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:51,440
Babe, what’s important in this battle is not to engage.

357
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,040
So what, tell me, was this whole episode not real?

358
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:58,320
You just figured that out?
It was all in the actors' heads.

359
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,240
No way!
-Yes way.

360
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,480
Enough!

361
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,200
Riki, what’s going on?

362
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:12,480
Did you see the African forecast...

363
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:16,160
Did you see how all her European vibes came out?

364
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,440
-Excuse me.

365
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,480
European vibes.
-You meant to say African vibes.

366
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:22,320
But something's spicy in my mouth.
-Drink some water.

367
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,560
This isn’t going to end well.

368
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:25,960
Oh, so I’m like...
-Excuse me.

369
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,040
No, I have another sentence here.

370
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:31,280
My mom took a self-defense course
a few weeks ago and finished with flying colors...

371
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:35,880
Ear and mouth...

372
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,280
Itamar!
-Itamar, come here!

373
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:44,000
Of course, in time...
-So beautiful...

374
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,400
Excuse me, excuse me.

375
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:55,680
About the silly fight between Smadar...
-Smadar.

